1
00:04:29,506 --> 00:04:30,881
Ma’am...

2
00:04:30,964 --> 00:04:33,256
I have a really bad
feeling about this place.

3
00:04:33,339 --> 00:04:36,089
So, let’s get out of here
as quickly as possible.

4
00:05:03,006 --> 00:05:05,006
Bring her alone.

5
00:05:05,256 --> 00:05:08,298
I don't want them
together even after death.

6
00:05:53,506 --> 00:05:55,089
Bring him!

7
00:06:06,173 --> 00:06:07,631
Go find him.

8
00:06:19,173 --> 00:06:21,089
James...

9
00:06:22,839 --> 00:06:25,881
James, where are you?

10
00:06:26,714 --> 00:06:28,714
Don't play with me.

11
00:06:28,798 --> 00:06:30,214
Come to me.

12
00:06:33,048 --> 00:06:34,756
James...

13
00:06:34,839 --> 00:06:37,131
where are you hiding?

14
00:06:37,214 --> 00:06:39,339
Come near me.

15
00:06:59,714 --> 00:07:01,548
James...

16
00:07:01,631 --> 00:07:04,089
why are you so scared?

17
00:07:04,798 --> 00:07:06,381
Come to me.

18
00:07:06,631 --> 00:07:08,423
Come and kiss me!

19
00:07:09,548 --> 00:07:11,798
Just like our first time!

20
00:07:11,881 --> 00:07:14,339
Come on! Get up!

21
00:07:44,339 --> 00:07:50,548
'SAMBHAVAM ADHYAYAM ONNU'
[THE INCIDENT-CHAPTER ONE]

22
00:10:55,798 --> 00:10:58,089
Why the hell didn’t you shoot?

23
00:11:51,423 --> 00:11:52,673
James...

24
00:11:53,298 --> 00:11:54,964
Where are you?

25
00:12:57,798 --> 00:13:00,048
Neethu’s bystander?

26
00:13:00,881 --> 00:13:03,048
Is Neethu’s bystander here?

27
00:13:03,339 --> 00:13:04,131
Yes.

28
00:13:04,214 --> 00:13:06,798
The doctor is calling you.
Please go inside.

29
00:13:07,339 --> 00:13:08,548
I’ll update you.

30
00:13:11,589 --> 00:13:12,839
Have a seat.

31
00:13:14,589 --> 00:13:15,423
Everything okay?

32
00:13:15,506 --> 00:13:17,006
Hey, don’t worry.

33
00:13:17,089 --> 00:13:18,131
She’s doing better now.

34
00:13:18,214 --> 00:13:20,548
Her due date is next
month, the 24th, right?

35
00:13:21,548 --> 00:13:23,256
Let’s plan to admit her on the 23rd.

36
00:13:23,381 --> 00:13:27,423
Come immediately if you notice
any pain or discomfort before then.

37
00:13:28,048 --> 00:13:30,089
Anand, why do you look so tense?

38
00:13:30,173 --> 00:13:32,214
You seem more worried than Neethu.

39
00:13:32,298 --> 00:13:32,923
No…

40
00:13:33,006 --> 00:13:34,964
-Are you stressed?
-No, no.

41
00:13:35,173 --> 00:13:37,631
Neethu is fine. Don’t worry at all.

42
00:13:39,506 --> 00:13:40,631
Alright then.

43
00:13:45,381 --> 00:13:47,923
You stay put. I’ll handle it.

44
00:13:48,131 --> 00:13:50,756
As if folding two clothes
is some huge task!

45
00:13:51,131 --> 00:13:53,548
I’ve kept some money inside.

46
00:13:54,548 --> 00:13:56,506
I have no choice but to go.

47
00:13:57,173 --> 00:13:59,339
Anyway, we still have one month, right?

48
00:13:59,423 --> 00:14:02,089
I’ll go there, check the situation…

49
00:14:02,173 --> 00:14:04,173
…and return once the medical’s done.

50
00:14:04,464 --> 00:14:06,548
Why are you overthinking this?

51
00:14:06,631 --> 00:14:08,798
I can handle things here.

52
00:14:08,881 --> 00:14:11,173
Moreover, aunty is here to help me.

53
00:14:12,548 --> 00:14:14,214
Call him if anything comes up.

54
00:14:14,339 --> 00:14:16,131
Sir, get ready. It’s time to leave.

55
00:14:18,423 --> 00:14:20,006
Eat on time, okay?

56
00:14:20,256 --> 00:14:21,964
Come on, get ready to go.

57
00:14:22,048 --> 00:14:23,173
Go… go.

58
00:14:23,423 --> 00:14:24,673
Are you sure you’re okay?

59
00:14:24,756 --> 00:14:26,839
I’m fine. Go ahead.
Don’t worry about me.

60
00:14:26,923 --> 00:14:27,881
Okay?

61
00:14:50,423 --> 00:14:52,089
Hey, get down here.

62
00:15:03,214 --> 00:15:04,506
So, he went to the Gulf, huh?

63
00:15:04,589 --> 00:15:05,839
Chetta, one tea, please.

64
00:15:05,923 --> 00:15:07,464
How do I get to Velloorkadu?

65
00:15:07,548 --> 00:15:09,214
Just get into that jeep.

66
00:15:17,006 --> 00:15:17,839
Yeah, go ahead.

67
00:15:17,923 --> 00:15:19,964
Hey, have you reached?
-Not yet.

68
00:15:20,048 --> 00:15:22,131
Listen, she had some mild pain.

69
00:15:22,214 --> 00:15:23,923
So we’re at the hospital now.

70
00:15:24,256 --> 00:15:25,964
What did the doctor say?!

71
00:15:26,131 --> 00:15:27,506
There’s a slight complication.

72
00:15:27,589 --> 00:15:30,506
They’re saying the delivery
might have to be done today itself.

73
00:15:31,798 --> 00:15:33,964
-I’ll come there right away.
-No need.

74
00:15:34,048 --> 00:15:35,548
You go ahead and join.

75
00:15:35,631 --> 00:15:37,256
You can’t get here anytime soon anyway.

76
00:15:37,339 --> 00:15:39,506
I just called to let you know.
No need to worry.

77
00:15:39,589 --> 00:15:41,381
-Aunty is there, right?
-Yes.

78
00:15:41,464 --> 00:15:42,881
Don’t worry. I’ll keep you posted.

79
00:15:42,964 --> 00:15:43,714
Okay.

80
00:15:49,839 --> 00:15:52,464
If you’re coming,
just get into the vehicle.

81
00:15:55,006 --> 00:15:57,048
-Chetta, cancel the tea.
-Huh?

82
00:16:02,673 --> 00:16:04,256
Where are you barging in!?

83
00:16:04,339 --> 00:16:05,506
Get in the backside!

84
00:16:08,298 --> 00:16:10,131
Who the heck is he?

85
00:16:39,548 --> 00:16:40,756
Are you hungry?

86
00:16:45,881 --> 00:16:47,506
What’s wrong, sir?

87
00:16:47,881 --> 00:16:49,214
Nothing.

88
00:16:49,298 --> 00:16:51,048
Is your SIM BSNL?

89
00:16:51,298 --> 00:16:52,131
No.

90
00:16:52,964 --> 00:16:55,256
Only BSNL gets signal here.

91
00:16:55,339 --> 00:16:57,506
If it’s urgent,
you can call from this phone.

92
00:17:00,631 --> 00:17:02,881
-Go on, make the call.
-No need.

93
00:17:03,006 --> 00:17:05,464
If you’re planning to call
your wife or someone...

94
00:17:05,548 --> 00:17:07,673
it’s better not to call from his phone.

95
00:17:07,756 --> 00:17:08,798
Right, Shaji?

96
00:17:12,048 --> 00:17:14,464
Ignore them. You go ahead, sir.

97
00:17:41,881 --> 00:17:43,548
Not answering?

98
00:17:43,631 --> 00:17:44,548
No.

99
00:17:47,423 --> 00:17:48,631
Sir...

100
00:17:50,714 --> 00:17:51,381
Hello?

101
00:17:51,589 --> 00:17:53,673
Why aren’t you answering me?

102
00:17:54,964 --> 00:17:55,423
Neethu?

103
00:18:02,381 --> 00:18:03,173
Okay.

104
00:18:05,423 --> 00:18:06,423
I’ve become a father.

105
00:18:06,589 --> 00:18:07,298
Wow!

106
00:18:07,631 --> 00:18:08,881
That’s wonderful news.

107
00:18:08,964 --> 00:18:09,881
Boy or girl?

108
00:18:09,964 --> 00:18:10,923
It’s a girl.

109
00:18:12,839 --> 00:18:15,339
Uncle’s been blessed with a baby girl.

110
00:18:16,131 --> 00:18:18,173
-Congrats, Uncle.
-Thank you.

111
00:18:18,256 --> 00:18:19,964
-Which grade are you in, dear?
-4th standard.

112
00:18:20,048 --> 00:18:20,964
Ah, nice!

113
00:18:31,589 --> 00:18:33,089
Shaji, listen...

114
00:18:33,173 --> 00:18:35,923
Did you hear about Ittichan’s daughter?

115
00:18:36,006 --> 00:18:39,923
Heard she’s shacked up
with someone in Bangalore.

116
00:18:40,923 --> 00:18:41,839
And also...

117
00:18:41,923 --> 00:18:45,923
Makes you wonder why we even
bother educating girls these days.

118
00:18:57,464 --> 00:18:58,548
Kid!

119
00:19:00,214 --> 00:19:02,089
Hey, open.

120
00:19:07,631 --> 00:19:08,756
Chetta!

121
00:19:12,339 --> 00:19:13,756
Where’s the closest hospital?

122
00:19:13,839 --> 00:19:15,214
Not close. We’ll have to go a bit.

123
00:19:15,298 --> 00:19:16,464
Hey!

124
00:19:16,548 --> 00:19:17,714
What the hell are you doing?

125
00:19:17,798 --> 00:19:18,673
Let the police come, you moron!

126
00:19:18,756 --> 00:19:20,964
I’m the damn police, you moron!
Hold him!

127
00:19:24,589 --> 00:19:25,839
Come on.

128
00:19:26,631 --> 00:19:28,006
Careful.

129
00:19:31,089 --> 00:19:32,714
Open the door.

130
00:19:34,381 --> 00:19:36,548
Chetta, open the door. I’ll hold him.

131
00:19:37,798 --> 00:19:39,923
-Start the vehicle.
-Uncle...

132
00:19:42,506 --> 00:19:44,548
Dear, go sit in the front.

133
00:19:53,006 --> 00:19:54,548
Hey, move aside!

134
00:19:56,548 --> 00:19:58,256
Get a rickshaw or something!

135
00:19:58,339 --> 00:19:59,464
Come on, man, let’s go!

136
00:21:10,339 --> 00:21:13,256
-Sir!
-Please, sit.

137
00:21:13,339 --> 00:21:15,589
-Anandu, right?
-Anand, sir.

138
00:21:15,839 --> 00:21:16,464
Yeah.

139
00:21:16,548 --> 00:21:18,131
That’s what I said.

140
00:21:18,214 --> 00:21:19,673
Where are you from in Kerala?

141
00:21:19,756 --> 00:21:20,548
Kochi.

142
00:21:20,631 --> 00:21:22,589
So, you’re a Kochi folk?

143
00:21:23,714 --> 00:21:24,798
Sir...

144
00:21:25,506 --> 00:21:28,173
Sir, I got this from him.

145
00:21:29,881 --> 00:21:32,589
Who? The guy who
just met with the accident?

146
00:21:37,381 --> 00:21:39,256
Peter John...

147
00:21:41,506 --> 00:21:43,006
Well...

148
00:21:43,089 --> 00:21:44,881
we’ll have to report this...

149
00:21:44,964 --> 00:21:46,048
at Perumalai station.

150
00:21:46,131 --> 00:21:47,214
Take a photo of this.

151
00:21:48,173 --> 00:21:49,339
Might come in handy later.

152
00:21:49,423 --> 00:21:51,423
Sir, he seems to be alright.

153
00:21:51,506 --> 00:21:53,173
But he has lost some blood.

154
00:21:53,256 --> 00:21:55,131
-Didn’t you inform his family?
-I will.

155
00:21:55,214 --> 00:21:57,298
Wait till they get here.

156
00:21:57,756 --> 00:22:00,423
And those jeep people...

157
00:22:00,506 --> 00:22:03,423
Let them go only after
completing all the formalities.

158
00:22:03,548 --> 00:22:04,548
There’s a reason for that.

159
00:22:04,631 --> 00:22:06,006
Did you have tea?

160
00:22:06,089 --> 00:22:06,631
No.

161
00:22:06,714 --> 00:22:07,423
Come.

162
00:22:07,506 --> 00:22:09,589
We get top-notch tea in the canteen here.

163
00:22:09,839 --> 00:22:10,798
Come, let’s grab some tea.

164
00:22:11,214 --> 00:22:12,381
Come on.

165
00:22:17,131 --> 00:22:18,589
Yeah, tell me.

166
00:22:18,673 --> 00:22:19,673
Your family?

167
00:22:19,756 --> 00:22:20,923
Just my wife.

168
00:22:21,006 --> 00:22:23,006
No… now I have a baby girl too.

169
00:22:23,298 --> 00:22:24,589
How old is your daughter?

170
00:22:24,673 --> 00:22:27,464
She was born today, just a few hours back.

171
00:22:29,298 --> 00:22:31,173
Then he owes us a treat, sir.

172
00:22:32,464 --> 00:22:33,506
Why not?

173
00:22:33,589 --> 00:22:35,756
So you haven’t even
seen your daughter yet?

174
00:22:37,048 --> 00:22:38,548
Do one thing…

175
00:22:38,631 --> 00:22:39,548
just go back.

176
00:22:39,631 --> 00:22:40,798
Join first, then head back.

177
00:22:40,881 --> 00:22:42,714
No, sir. It’s fine.

178
00:22:44,964 --> 00:22:46,256
Wait…

179
00:22:46,589 --> 00:22:47,798
Here's better...

180
00:22:47,881 --> 00:22:49,048
Go back on Sunday.

181
00:22:49,131 --> 00:22:51,173
Take a couple of days and then come back.

182
00:22:52,339 --> 00:22:55,756
It’s not like you’ve got some
huge responsibility here!

183
00:22:56,048 --> 00:22:58,214
No better place to get transferred anyway!

184
00:22:58,298 --> 00:22:59,131
Yeah… yeah.

185
00:23:02,673 --> 00:23:04,923
A disciplinary action, huh?

186
00:23:05,006 --> 00:23:06,548
You’re not a troublemaker, right?

187
00:23:06,631 --> 00:23:07,631
No, sir…

188
00:23:07,839 --> 00:23:11,006
We faced complications
during my wife’s pregnancy.

189
00:23:11,506 --> 00:23:16,173
Almost every day after duty,
I couldn’t sleep because of the tension.

190
00:23:16,256 --> 00:23:19,548
Then one day, I was on
guard duty… and I dozed off.

191
00:23:19,839 --> 00:23:22,548
I missed saluting the SHO
when he came in.

192
00:23:24,298 --> 00:23:25,923
No wonder…

193
00:23:26,006 --> 00:23:30,131
No wonder you put on a whole show
when I walked in.

194
00:23:30,631 --> 00:23:32,006
Listen…

195
00:23:32,089 --> 00:23:34,464
Respect should reflect in your conduct.

196
00:23:34,798 --> 00:23:38,256
Not just in snapping a salute
the moment you see someone.

197
00:23:38,339 --> 00:23:40,798
We don’t follow that culture here.

198
00:23:41,339 --> 00:23:43,339
What about your parents?

199
00:23:45,214 --> 00:23:47,214
I’ve never seen my father.

200
00:23:47,298 --> 00:23:49,256
He was also in the police department.

201
00:23:50,089 --> 00:23:52,756
He passed away just before I was born.

202
00:23:53,131 --> 00:23:56,589
That shock broke my mother mentally.

203
00:23:56,673 --> 00:23:58,589
Didn’t take long… she left too.

204
00:23:59,631 --> 00:24:03,589
Since it was a love marriage,
my wife’s family doesn’t talk to us.

205
00:24:04,423 --> 00:24:05,923
Now that you have a child…

206
00:24:06,006 --> 00:24:07,881
things will slowly fall into place.

207
00:24:09,339 --> 00:24:11,256
Wasn’t very different for me either.

208
00:24:11,339 --> 00:24:12,214
-Really?
-Yeah!

209
00:24:12,298 --> 00:24:14,798
He was in love with a girl.

210
00:24:15,256 --> 00:24:21,256
Her father was hell-bent on
stopping the marriage at any cost.

211
00:24:21,339 --> 00:24:23,464
Ready to kill him if it came to that.

212
00:24:23,548 --> 00:24:25,423
We didn’t think twice.

213
00:24:25,548 --> 00:24:28,798
Taking the girl out of her house,
getting them married…

214
00:24:28,881 --> 00:24:31,339
And sending them
straight to their first night…

215
00:24:31,423 --> 00:24:34,089
Handled top to bottom
by the Kerala Police!

216
00:24:34,506 --> 00:24:36,214
But now…

217
00:24:36,298 --> 00:24:39,673
He and his father-in-law
are thick as thieves.

218
00:24:40,881 --> 00:24:43,173
That’s all it takes, Anandu.

219
00:24:44,256 --> 00:24:46,006
Everything will be alright.

220
00:24:49,589 --> 00:24:50,923
Yes, Rasheed?

221
00:24:51,006 --> 00:24:52,506
Sir, there’s an issue.

222
00:24:52,589 --> 00:24:54,048
What issue?

223
00:24:54,131 --> 00:24:56,923
While passing through the forest road…

224
00:24:57,548 --> 00:25:00,798
We noticed a vehicle parked
suspiciously and checked it.

225
00:25:00,923 --> 00:25:02,839
Some youngsters were inside.

226
00:25:02,923 --> 00:25:05,589
They were trying to shoot some video.
They’re Tamilians, sir.

227
00:25:05,673 --> 00:25:07,673
There are 1-2 girls with them too.

228
00:25:08,673 --> 00:25:11,006
Sir, he’s stepped in and blocked them!

229
00:25:12,464 --> 00:25:13,964
Who? Reji?

230
00:25:14,048 --> 00:25:15,006
Yes, sir.

231
00:25:19,798 --> 00:25:22,964
Looks like they have
influence at higher levels.

232
00:25:23,048 --> 00:25:25,006
I don’t think I can handle this.

233
00:25:25,089 --> 00:25:26,964
Sir, can you come here quickly?

234
00:25:30,339 --> 00:25:32,714
What the hell is wrong with him!?

235
00:25:35,798 --> 00:25:37,506
Please don’t create trouble.

236
00:25:37,589 --> 00:25:38,714
The SI will be here soon.

237
00:25:38,798 --> 00:25:40,423
Why should I talk to him, sir?

238
00:25:40,506 --> 00:25:42,589
Even now, we are standing in our area.

239
00:25:42,673 --> 00:25:44,381
Son, just listen to me.

240
00:25:44,464 --> 00:25:47,464
Beyond this point, only the
Forest Department has permission.

241
00:25:47,548 --> 00:25:49,173
This is a restricted zone.

242
00:25:49,256 --> 00:25:50,964
Sir, I understand that.

243
00:25:51,048 --> 00:25:53,131
But why is he yelling at me like that?

244
00:25:53,756 --> 00:25:55,631
Who is he? Some forest ranger?

245
00:25:55,714 --> 00:25:57,381
Tell him to calm down first.

246
00:25:57,464 --> 00:25:59,131
Or you can’t imagine what happens next!

247
00:25:59,798 --> 00:26:02,798
Listen, this area falls
under our father’s control.

248
00:26:03,214 --> 00:26:04,964
If you create trouble for us here…

249
00:26:05,048 --> 00:26:07,131
You can forget about
wearing that uniform again!

250
00:26:07,214 --> 00:26:10,131
If you want to keep your job,
leave right now!

251
00:26:10,339 --> 00:26:12,298
What is it, Dad?
Didn’t I tell you I’ll call you later!?

252
00:26:16,548 --> 00:26:18,048
Hey, let go of my hand!

253
00:26:18,131 --> 00:26:19,339
Switch it off!

254
00:26:20,381 --> 00:26:22,173
I said switch it off now!

255
00:26:23,298 --> 00:26:25,798
Didn’t I warn you clearly
the first time, you wretches!?

256
00:26:25,881 --> 00:26:27,214
Get out of here right now!

257
00:26:31,673 --> 00:26:33,798
Reji, Reji, no!

258
00:26:33,881 --> 00:26:35,798
Reji, stop!

259
00:26:39,756 --> 00:26:41,256
Hey, no!

260
00:26:41,339 --> 00:26:42,423
Reji!

261
00:26:42,506 --> 00:26:43,714
Reji, stop!

262
00:26:43,798 --> 00:26:44,839
Listen to me!

263
00:27:30,589 --> 00:27:32,756
-Where?
-A little deeper inside, sir.

264
00:27:45,381 --> 00:27:47,506
-Did you identify the person?
-No, sir.

265
00:27:47,589 --> 00:27:49,506
Something has chewed off his face.

266
00:27:49,589 --> 00:27:51,839
And his clothes are
soaked in mud too, sir.

267
00:27:51,923 --> 00:27:53,714
Looks like he fell into a marsh.

268
00:28:10,173 --> 00:28:12,089
Did you inform forensics?

269
00:28:12,173 --> 00:28:13,423
They’re on the way, sir.

270
00:28:13,506 --> 00:28:15,423
It’ll take some time to reach here.

271
00:28:35,298 --> 00:28:36,506
What’s gotten into you?

272
00:28:36,589 --> 00:28:38,464
You seem more damn bothered
than the Forest Department!

273
00:28:38,548 --> 00:28:42,173
Just because I gave you some freedom,
don’t push your luck with me!

274
00:28:43,798 --> 00:28:45,631
Did you collect their details?

275
00:28:45,714 --> 00:28:46,506
Yes, sir.

276
00:28:46,714 --> 00:28:49,631
Sir… doesn’t that look
like a policeman’s body?

277
00:28:50,048 --> 00:28:52,589
Shouldn’t we probe that angle?

278
00:28:52,673 --> 00:28:54,798
Oh, as if we’re idiots!

279
00:28:56,464 --> 00:28:58,714
That’s a policeman from
Perumalai station, sir.

280
00:28:58,798 --> 00:29:00,589
But they’re not answering calls right now.

281
00:29:00,673 --> 00:29:01,881
Who’s this?

282
00:29:02,298 --> 00:29:04,298
I’m the new CPO, sir.

283
00:29:04,381 --> 00:29:06,839
Hey, do you have the number
of anyone from Perumalai station?

284
00:29:06,923 --> 00:29:07,589
No, sir.

285
00:29:07,673 --> 00:29:10,089
Sir, I have an ASI’s number from there.

286
00:29:10,173 --> 00:29:10,714
Give it.

287
00:29:13,173 --> 00:29:14,673
-2-0
-2-0…

288
00:29:14,756 --> 00:29:16,964
-9-5-0-3
-9-5-0-3.

289
00:29:23,131 --> 00:29:25,214
-You try reaching them too.
-Okay, sir.

290
00:29:25,714 --> 00:29:27,839
Report to the station when
the forensic team arrives.

291
00:29:27,923 --> 00:29:29,298
I’ll be at the station.

292
00:29:33,089 --> 00:29:34,339
I’ll come along.

293
00:29:34,631 --> 00:29:37,089
If anything comes up, call me.

294
00:29:37,714 --> 00:29:39,214
Move in.

295
00:30:21,464 --> 00:30:23,173
Hey, Peter!

296
00:30:26,381 --> 00:30:27,839
Muthuvel!

297
00:30:30,089 --> 00:30:31,548
PETER!

298
00:30:34,339 --> 00:30:35,923
MUTHUVEL!

299
00:30:38,381 --> 00:30:40,714
Can anyone hear me?

300
00:30:41,839 --> 00:30:44,714
CAN ANYONE HEAR ME!?

301
00:30:51,714 --> 00:30:53,714
P3 calling, P3 calling!

302
00:30:53,798 --> 00:30:55,631
Can anyone hear me?

303
00:30:55,714 --> 00:30:57,089
I repeat, can anyone hear me?

304
00:30:57,173 --> 00:30:58,381
Sir!

305
00:30:58,464 --> 00:30:59,714
Hello!?

306
00:30:59,839 --> 00:31:01,548
Isn’t this that officer’s handset?

307
00:31:01,631 --> 00:31:03,548
Can anyone hear me?

308
00:31:03,964 --> 00:31:06,589
We came into this forest as a team, sir.

309
00:31:06,673 --> 00:31:08,506
Now the rest are missing.

310
00:31:08,589 --> 00:31:10,173
I'm the only one left.

311
00:31:10,256 --> 00:31:12,381
Please save me somehow, sir.

312
00:31:12,548 --> 00:31:13,589
Hello?

313
00:31:13,673 --> 00:31:14,839
Sir! Sir! Sir! Sir!

314
00:31:14,923 --> 00:31:17,506
My name is Stephen, sir. Can you hear me?
Can you hear me?

315
00:31:17,589 --> 00:31:19,214
Yes, I can. I can hear you.

316
00:31:19,298 --> 00:31:20,839
My leg is injured, sir.

317
00:31:20,923 --> 00:31:22,548
Feels like I’m dying from the pain.

318
00:31:22,631 --> 00:31:24,298
Please do something, sir.

319
00:31:24,381 --> 00:31:25,756
Sir, this is Kerala Police.

320
00:31:25,839 --> 00:31:29,673
One officer from your department has
met with an accident on the forest road.

321
00:31:29,756 --> 00:31:32,381
His handset is currently
with the Kerala Police.

322
00:31:32,464 --> 00:31:35,339
Inform your control room
or report to your station.

323
00:31:35,423 --> 00:31:37,548
Sir… sir… please listen to me, sir.

324
00:31:37,923 --> 00:31:40,173
I'm trying for a long while.

325
00:31:40,256 --> 00:31:42,381
But no one's answering.

326
00:31:43,089 --> 00:31:45,756
I can’t even move, sir.

327
00:31:45,839 --> 00:31:48,173
I’ve lost a lot of blood…

328
00:31:48,256 --> 00:31:50,589
I'm near the temple, sir.

329
00:31:50,673 --> 00:31:52,506
Please come help me, sir.

330
00:31:52,589 --> 00:31:55,089
Sir, this is risky.
It’s outside our limits.

331
00:31:55,173 --> 00:31:59,214
On top of that, we wont understand
anything if we get deep inside it.

332
00:32:00,798 --> 00:32:02,173
Sir...

333
00:32:02,256 --> 00:32:03,923
are you here, sir?

334
00:32:04,298 --> 00:32:06,631
Please speak something, sir.

335
00:32:10,714 --> 00:32:12,548
Pull over the jeep.

336
00:32:28,464 --> 00:32:30,089
Hey, do you have network?

337
00:32:30,173 --> 00:32:31,256
No, sir.

338
00:32:32,006 --> 00:32:34,381
What the heck is wrong with him!?

339
00:32:35,506 --> 00:32:37,673
Thats a policeman screaming for life, sir.

340
00:32:38,173 --> 00:32:39,548
Sir...

341
00:32:39,631 --> 00:32:41,548
are you in line?

342
00:32:43,173 --> 00:32:43,714
Sir...

343
00:32:43,798 --> 00:32:45,673
I'm gonna have a baby, sir.

344
00:32:47,714 --> 00:32:51,339
After years of waiting…

345
00:32:51,673 --> 00:32:55,256
If you help me…
I can at least see my child.

346
00:32:55,798 --> 00:32:58,173
I’m begging you like you’re God, sir.

347
00:32:58,256 --> 00:32:59,964
Sir, please… sir!

348
00:33:00,423 --> 00:33:04,048
Switch off that damn thing.
Hey, start the vehicle.

349
00:33:04,256 --> 00:33:07,089
Sir, he says he’s lost a lot of blood.

350
00:33:07,173 --> 00:33:09,631
If we don’t help him now,
he’ll bleed out to death there, sir.

351
00:33:09,714 --> 00:33:11,048
So what?

352
00:33:11,131 --> 00:33:12,756
That’s not our responsibility.

353
00:33:12,839 --> 00:33:14,589
Sir, I know it isn’t.

354
00:33:14,673 --> 00:33:17,131
But if we act now,
he might at least live to see his child.

355
00:33:17,214 --> 00:33:18,756
It’s a life, sir.

356
00:33:18,839 --> 00:33:20,298
What nonsense are you talking?

357
00:33:20,381 --> 00:33:22,089
Have you ever stepped
into this forest before?

358
00:33:22,173 --> 00:33:23,756
I’m a local around here.

359
00:33:24,673 --> 00:33:27,089
Sir, this place is dangerous!

360
00:33:27,173 --> 00:33:29,464
If you want to go in trusting
some random guy, go ahead.

361
00:33:29,548 --> 00:33:30,673
I’m not coming.

362
00:33:30,756 --> 00:33:32,214
Sir, are you scared?

363
00:33:32,298 --> 00:33:33,506
Scared?

364
00:33:33,839 --> 00:33:34,964
Me?

365
00:34:24,423 --> 00:34:25,589
Sir!

366
00:34:25,673 --> 00:34:26,423
Hey!

367
00:34:27,798 --> 00:34:29,298
Hey, move away!

368
00:34:29,381 --> 00:34:30,631
What are you doing?

369
00:34:30,923 --> 00:34:32,756
I’ll shoot him down!

370
00:34:34,339 --> 00:34:35,798
Put the gun down.

371
00:34:35,881 --> 00:34:37,964
Come on, let me go!

372
00:34:38,048 --> 00:34:39,673
Hey, hand over that gun!

373
00:34:40,214 --> 00:34:42,589
Listen to me. Put the gun down!

374
00:34:42,673 --> 00:34:44,673
I’ll kill him! I swear I will!

375
00:34:45,339 --> 00:34:47,339
Hey, unlock this!

376
00:34:54,964 --> 00:34:56,381
Don't shoot!

377
00:34:56,464 --> 00:34:58,589
Tell him to unlock this!

378
00:35:07,048 --> 00:35:09,464
Hey, hurry up!

379
00:35:09,548 --> 00:35:11,048
Go, go!

380
00:35:11,589 --> 00:35:14,423
-Hey, stop right there!
-Come on!

381
00:35:14,506 --> 00:35:16,506
Hey, are you okay!?

382
00:35:16,589 --> 00:35:18,381
Peter, where’s the first-aid box?

383
00:35:18,464 --> 00:35:20,131
-I’ll get it right away, sir.
-Das…

384
00:35:20,214 --> 00:35:21,423
Are you okay?

385
00:38:16,131 --> 00:38:17,381
Peter!

386
00:38:19,006 --> 00:38:21,089
If you see them, don’t shoot.

387
00:38:21,173 --> 00:38:23,298
Inform me first.

388
00:38:23,381 --> 00:38:25,506
Sir, do we really need to go further?

389
00:38:35,006 --> 00:38:35,881
Sir…

390
00:38:35,964 --> 00:38:38,548
I don’t believe in ghosts
or evil spirits that much.

391
00:38:38,631 --> 00:38:42,173
But ever since we entered here,
something feels very wrong.

392
00:38:44,214 --> 00:38:45,256
Sir…

393
00:38:45,631 --> 00:38:47,048
Since my childhood…

394
00:38:47,131 --> 00:38:50,339
there's a story everyone in the
village keeps talking about, sir.

395
00:38:50,423 --> 00:38:53,839
Many years ago, there was a temple here.

396
00:38:54,131 --> 00:38:56,673
To drive away bad times
and bring good fortune…

397
00:38:56,756 --> 00:38:58,798
People used to pray to that deity.

398
00:38:59,006 --> 00:39:02,798
The day people began
offering human sacrifices…

399
00:39:02,881 --> 00:39:05,464
That was the day all the troubles began.

400
00:39:05,923 --> 00:39:08,006
From that day onwards, on this soil…

401
00:39:08,089 --> 00:39:09,714
No blood should be spilled…

402
00:39:09,798 --> 00:39:12,798
And no sound should cross a certain limit.

403
00:39:43,048 --> 00:39:45,631
Muthuvel, you go that way.
I’ll take this route.

404
00:39:45,714 --> 00:39:48,173
Oh no, sir, please listen
to me for heaven’s sake!

405
00:39:48,548 --> 00:39:50,089
Hey, Muthuvel…

406
00:39:50,173 --> 00:39:52,214
In those times, there were
plenty of stories like this.

407
00:39:52,298 --> 00:39:53,798
But we have to catch them no matter what.

408
00:39:53,881 --> 00:39:55,131
We don’t have any other choice.

409
00:39:55,214 --> 00:39:57,339
Go! Please understand. Go!

410
00:40:23,339 --> 00:40:25,631
Sir, please save me!

411
00:40:25,964 --> 00:40:27,173
Sir!

412
00:40:27,506 --> 00:40:28,964
Sir!

413
00:40:41,173 --> 00:40:42,798
Muthuvel!

414
00:40:44,589 --> 00:40:45,589
Sir!

415
00:40:45,673 --> 00:40:46,756
What happened, Muthuvel?

416
00:40:46,839 --> 00:40:47,631
Them...!

417
00:40:49,631 --> 00:40:50,839
Hey!

418
00:40:50,923 --> 00:40:52,506
Calm down. Surrender yourself.

419
00:40:54,548 --> 00:40:55,673
Hey!

420
00:41:25,631 --> 00:41:27,339
James!

421
00:41:27,423 --> 00:41:29,256
Where are you?

422
00:42:15,839 --> 00:42:17,131
Muthuvel?

423
00:42:17,214 --> 00:42:18,714
Hey, Muthuvel!

424
00:42:19,423 --> 00:42:20,756
Muthuvel!

425
00:42:20,923 --> 00:42:22,214
Muthuvel!

426
00:42:22,298 --> 00:42:23,881
Hey, Muthuvel!

427
00:42:23,964 --> 00:42:24,964
Peter!

428
00:42:25,048 --> 00:42:26,714
Where did you go?

429
00:42:47,256 --> 00:42:48,964
Sir, should we really go any further?

430
00:42:49,048 --> 00:42:51,589
What happened? Already tired?

431
00:42:51,673 --> 00:42:53,214
Come on.

432
00:43:01,298 --> 00:43:02,839
Hey, Reji...

433
00:43:03,214 --> 00:43:07,214
You still buy into those
tall tales people spin?

434
00:43:11,881 --> 00:43:14,464
Sir, what are the locals
saying about this place?

435
00:43:14,548 --> 00:43:16,756
They’ve got plenty of stories.

436
00:43:16,839 --> 00:43:19,298
Many people have gone
missing in this forest.

437
00:43:19,381 --> 00:43:23,798
The first missing case was reported
in our station back in 1960.

438
00:43:24,256 --> 00:43:27,673
A girl who worked at a nearby estate.

439
00:43:27,756 --> 00:43:30,964
The estate owner was a Portuguese lady.

440
00:43:31,131 --> 00:43:33,798
People said she had some strange issues.

441
00:43:33,881 --> 00:43:37,339
She married a man much younger than her.

442
00:43:37,423 --> 00:43:40,881
That man was having an affair
with the girl who worked there.

443
00:43:42,839 --> 00:43:45,381
The Portuguese lady
caught them red-handed.

444
00:43:45,464 --> 00:43:47,923
She dragged both of them into the
forest and dumped their bodies there.

445
00:43:48,298 --> 00:43:50,756
Later, she also died.

446
00:43:54,339 --> 00:43:57,798
People say all three of their
spirits still wander around here.

447
00:43:59,173 --> 00:44:02,839
After I took charge, we recovered
a body from this forest once.

448
00:44:02,923 --> 00:44:06,673
Almost around the same place
where we found the body today.

449
00:44:06,756 --> 00:44:09,423
That man too... hadn’t been dead for long.

450
00:44:09,506 --> 00:44:11,714
The body had just started decomposing.

451
00:44:11,881 --> 00:44:13,089
But...

452
00:44:13,173 --> 00:44:15,381
That body had no head!

453
00:44:20,798 --> 00:44:22,756
Aren’t you coming?

454
00:44:25,256 --> 00:44:27,339
Sir, then what happened next?

455
00:44:27,423 --> 00:44:29,089
What else could happen?

456
00:44:29,173 --> 00:44:32,131
We couldn’t identify the
body without the head.

457
00:44:32,214 --> 00:44:36,339
Locals started spinning stories,
said it was that foreigner.

458
00:44:36,423 --> 00:44:37,256
Who?

459
00:44:37,339 --> 00:44:39,798
That man who supposedly
died almost 80 years ago!

460
00:44:39,881 --> 00:44:42,381
Bloody nonsense,
their wild fantasies!

461
00:44:42,631 --> 00:44:44,339
Then did you ever find the head, sir?

462
00:44:44,423 --> 00:44:45,506
No chance.

463
00:44:45,589 --> 00:44:47,923
We searched everywhere, but found nothing.

464
00:44:48,006 --> 00:44:50,089
Back then, we never came
this deep into the forest.

465
00:44:50,173 --> 00:44:52,131
Honestly, this is my first
time coming this far inside.

466
00:44:52,214 --> 00:44:54,381
But back then, we did recover a skull.

467
00:44:54,714 --> 00:44:56,881
Though it looked quite old.

468
00:44:57,089 --> 00:44:58,381
Whose was it?

469
00:44:58,464 --> 00:44:59,298
No idea.

470
00:44:59,423 --> 00:45:01,589
It could have belonged to that foreigner.

471
00:45:05,381 --> 00:45:07,923
Sir, shouldn’t we inform
the forest authorities?

472
00:45:08,006 --> 00:45:10,006
What? Are you scared too?

473
00:45:10,089 --> 00:45:10,673
No...

474
00:45:10,756 --> 00:45:12,714
According to him...

475
00:45:12,798 --> 00:45:14,298
this falls under another state.

476
00:45:14,381 --> 00:45:18,048
By the time we inform them and
they relay it to the forest department...

477
00:45:18,131 --> 00:45:19,756
he might already be dead.

478
00:45:19,839 --> 00:45:23,298
-We’re talking about saving a life here-
-Can you hear me?

479
00:45:23,589 --> 00:45:24,173
Have you arrived?

480
00:45:24,256 --> 00:45:28,048
Where? Where are you? We’re on the way.

481
00:45:28,131 --> 00:45:30,631
Sir, there’s a huge tree here.

482
00:45:30,714 --> 00:45:32,339
It’s covered with creepers...

483
00:45:32,423 --> 00:45:33,964
-I’m right under it.
-What?

484
00:45:34,048 --> 00:45:35,839
Sir... err...

485
00:45:35,923 --> 00:45:38,464
-It’s like a money plant, sir.
-What plant?

486
00:45:38,548 --> 00:45:40,631
Some kind of creeper! You heard me!?

487
00:45:40,714 --> 00:45:42,923
Sir, can you hear me!?

488
00:45:55,673 --> 00:45:58,089
Sir, about that hospital matter...

489
00:45:58,673 --> 00:46:00,339
Yeah, let me try calling Joshy.

490
00:46:02,214 --> 00:46:04,714
-Hello, sir?
-Joshy, what’s the update?

491
00:46:04,798 --> 00:46:05,964
Sir, he regained consciousness.

492
00:46:06,048 --> 00:46:07,548
He’s blabbering without any sense.

493
00:46:07,631 --> 00:46:08,839
Did you inform his family?

494
00:46:08,923 --> 00:46:10,048
Yes, sir.

495
00:46:10,131 --> 00:46:12,464
I didn’t explain anything.
Just asked them to come.

496
00:46:12,548 --> 00:46:14,381
They’re near the border.
They’ll reach soon.

497
00:46:14,464 --> 00:46:15,631
Inform me if there’s anything else.
-Okay, sir.

498
00:46:16,506 --> 00:46:18,131
-Listen, he regained—

499
00:46:37,048 --> 00:46:39,756
Sir, hello? Hello?

500
00:46:39,839 --> 00:46:41,548
Hello? Hello?

501
00:46:41,631 --> 00:46:43,006
Can you hear me?

502
00:46:43,089 --> 00:46:44,589
-Sir, can you hear me?
-Hello? Hello?

503
00:46:45,214 --> 00:46:47,048
Just handle this, man.

504
00:46:47,131 --> 00:46:49,173
Sir, can you hear me?

505
00:46:49,589 --> 00:46:50,381
Hello?

506
00:46:50,464 --> 00:46:51,173
Sir...

507
00:46:51,256 --> 00:46:53,089
We’re near the temple.

508
00:46:53,173 --> 00:46:54,923
I’m somewhere close to it, sir.

509
00:46:55,006 --> 00:46:56,381
I’m nearby.

510
00:46:56,464 --> 00:46:58,756
Nearby where?
Ask him for another landmark.

511
00:46:58,964 --> 00:47:01,214
Sir... where exactly are you?

512
00:47:01,381 --> 00:47:04,464
Sir… it’s all trees here.

513
00:47:04,548 --> 00:47:06,923
What do you expect
in a forest? Trees or ti--

514
00:47:07,464 --> 00:47:08,839
Go on, go on.

515
00:47:08,923 --> 00:47:10,839
Sir, is it left or right from here?

516
00:47:10,923 --> 00:47:12,756
Sir, it’s left.

517
00:47:14,339 --> 00:47:16,756
No, no! Right, sir.

518
00:47:17,131 --> 00:47:18,548
Are you sure, sir?

519
00:47:18,631 --> 00:47:20,714
-Yes, sir. It’s right.
-Check that side.

520
00:47:31,173 --> 00:47:32,673
Their ASI is calling.

521
00:47:33,714 --> 00:47:34,881
Hello?

522
00:47:35,839 --> 00:47:37,089
Hello, who is this?

523
00:47:37,173 --> 00:47:39,964
Sir, I’m Ashokan,
in charge at Velloorkadu station.

524
00:47:40,048 --> 00:47:40,714
Yes, tell me, sir.

525
00:47:40,798 --> 00:47:42,714
Sir, we received information this morning.

526
00:47:42,798 --> 00:47:46,673
That an officer from your
station is trapped in this forest.

527
00:47:46,756 --> 00:47:48,673
We tried contacting you.

528
00:47:48,756 --> 00:47:50,839
Since we couldn’t reach you,
we came here ourselves.

529
00:47:50,923 --> 00:47:51,964
Forest?

530
00:47:52,048 --> 00:47:52,923
Which area?

531
00:47:53,006 --> 00:47:55,631
Sir, there’s an old temple
deep inside the forest, right?

532
00:47:55,714 --> 00:47:56,673
Seems to be near that.

533
00:47:56,756 --> 00:47:58,673
Oh, temple? Which temple?

534
00:47:58,756 --> 00:48:02,256
An old one… with a crow statue.

535
00:48:02,339 --> 00:48:03,881
Somewhere near that premises.

536
00:48:04,756 --> 00:48:06,381
That place?

537
00:48:06,631 --> 00:48:08,464
Where exactly are you now?

538
00:48:08,714 --> 00:48:10,339
We’re close to it.

539
00:48:10,423 --> 00:48:12,506
Almost near the premises.

540
00:48:13,173 --> 00:48:15,214
Have you lost your minds?

541
00:48:18,214 --> 00:48:20,423
No one from here would ever go there.

542
00:48:20,506 --> 00:48:21,923
First, leave that place immediately.

543
00:48:22,006 --> 00:48:24,464
Sir, we spoke to him just a while ago.

544
00:48:25,881 --> 00:48:27,548
Doesn’t he have a name?

545
00:48:27,631 --> 00:48:29,673
I think his name is Stephen.

546
00:48:29,756 --> 00:48:31,423
Sir, you don’t even know his name?

547
00:48:31,506 --> 00:48:33,964
Why enter the forest
without basic clarity?

548
00:48:34,048 --> 00:48:35,089
It’s Stephen, sir.

549
00:48:35,173 --> 00:48:37,173
Yes, his name is definitely Stephen.

550
00:48:37,256 --> 00:48:38,923
No one here goes by that name!

551
00:48:39,006 --> 00:48:40,631
First, get out of there!

552
00:48:40,714 --> 00:48:41,631
Please!

553
00:48:59,631 --> 00:49:02,298
Sir, can you hear me? Can you hear me?

554
00:49:03,839 --> 00:49:06,131
Sir, are you still on the line?

555
00:49:06,214 --> 00:49:08,048
Sir, it’s him.

556
00:49:08,589 --> 00:49:10,923
Sir, this feels very off. Let’s leave.

557
00:49:11,006 --> 00:49:13,131
Where are you, sir?

558
00:49:15,381 --> 00:49:17,423
Hey, where are you now?

559
00:49:17,506 --> 00:49:19,548
We’ve been wandering
around here for so long!

560
00:49:19,631 --> 00:49:20,548
Who are you?

561
00:49:20,631 --> 00:49:23,423
Sir, come on! My name is Stephen!

562
00:49:24,839 --> 00:49:26,589
Are you really from Perumalai station?

563
00:49:26,673 --> 00:49:27,673
Yes, sir.

564
00:49:27,756 --> 00:49:30,881
When we called there, they said
no one named Stephen works there.

565
00:49:30,964 --> 00:49:32,548
Who told you that?

566
00:49:32,631 --> 00:49:35,673
Why would I lie to you
in a situation like this?

567
00:49:36,256 --> 00:49:39,464
My name is Stephen George.
I’m the Inspector of Perumalai Station.

568
00:49:39,548 --> 00:49:40,714
Damn! Hold this!

569
00:49:40,798 --> 00:49:43,131
Sir... please believe me.

570
00:49:43,256 --> 00:49:45,381
I’m telling you the truth, sir.

571
00:49:45,548 --> 00:49:47,089
Sir...

572
00:49:47,714 --> 00:49:50,214
I can’t beg anymore.

573
00:49:50,298 --> 00:49:52,423
My name is Stephen.

574
00:49:52,506 --> 00:49:55,256
Sir, shall we call that ASI once more?

575
00:49:55,339 --> 00:49:57,089
Please help me, sir.

576
00:49:58,548 --> 00:50:01,631
If the caste issue escalates,
or if they file a complaint, inform me.

577
00:50:01,714 --> 00:50:03,048
Understood?

578
00:50:07,548 --> 00:50:09,298
What’s wrong with you, sir?

579
00:50:09,381 --> 00:50:10,673
Haven’t you left that place yet?

580
00:50:10,756 --> 00:50:14,256
Sir, please listen fully
to what I’m saying.

581
00:50:14,339 --> 00:50:17,339
This morning, there was an
accident on the forest route.

582
00:50:17,548 --> 00:50:21,464
The victim was a police officer
named Peter from your station.

583
00:50:21,548 --> 00:50:23,214
We admitted him to the hospital.

584
00:50:23,298 --> 00:50:27,131
After some time,
a message came to his handset.

585
00:50:27,214 --> 00:50:30,089
It said someone was
trapped in this forest.

586
00:50:30,173 --> 00:50:34,589
The information we received said it was
SI Stephen George from Perumalai Station.

587
00:50:35,464 --> 00:50:37,048
Apart from this,

588
00:50:37,131 --> 00:50:39,423
we also recovered a body
from the forest this morning.

589
00:50:39,506 --> 00:50:41,839
That too... of a policeman.

590
00:50:41,923 --> 00:50:46,131
Sir, we suspect it might be someone
from Perumalai Police Station.

591
00:50:46,423 --> 00:50:49,131
Sir, please understand what I’m saying.

592
00:50:49,214 --> 00:50:50,839
There was a meeting at our station today.

593
00:50:50,923 --> 00:50:52,298
All of us were present.

594
00:50:52,381 --> 00:50:54,089
There are only two SIs at our station.

595
00:50:54,173 --> 00:50:56,506
One is Ram,
and the other is Principal SI Kumar.

596
00:50:56,589 --> 00:50:59,298
There is no one named
Peter or Stephen at our station!

597
00:51:07,506 --> 00:51:10,256
Then, sir... who are we talking to?

598
00:51:10,339 --> 00:51:11,756
Why are you asking me all this?

599
00:51:11,839 --> 00:51:13,589
You’re just wandering around for nothing!

600
00:51:13,673 --> 00:51:15,256
And troubling me on top of that!

601
00:51:15,964 --> 00:51:19,256
Sir, he sounds very sure.
He’s still on the line.

602
00:51:19,339 --> 00:51:21,006
Please speak to him.

603
00:51:21,423 --> 00:51:23,423
-Sir?
-Tell me, sir.

604
00:51:23,506 --> 00:51:25,714
Sir, the ASI from your
station is on the call.

605
00:51:25,798 --> 00:51:27,006
Please speak to him.

606
00:51:27,089 --> 00:51:28,006
ASI?

607
00:51:28,089 --> 00:51:29,298
Isn’t it Muthuvel?

608
00:51:29,381 --> 00:51:31,423
Muthuvel, it’s me- Stephen.

609
00:51:31,506 --> 00:51:33,131
Where did all of you go!?

610
00:51:33,214 --> 00:51:35,006
I’m all alone here!

611
00:51:35,089 --> 00:51:36,673
Where are the others?

612
00:51:36,756 --> 00:51:38,673
Please come here quickly.

613
00:51:38,756 --> 00:51:41,089
Wait... what’s his full name again?

614
00:51:41,173 --> 00:51:42,756
Stephen George, right?

615
00:51:42,839 --> 00:51:44,756
Yes. Stephen George.

616
00:51:45,006 --> 00:51:47,798
Ask the full name of that Muthuvel.

617
00:51:49,548 --> 00:51:52,173
Sir, what’s Muthuvel’s full name?

618
00:51:52,256 --> 00:51:54,173
Why are you asking all that, sir?

619
00:51:54,339 --> 00:51:56,006
Just tell us, sir!

620
00:51:56,173 --> 00:51:58,256
Muthuvel Mariyappan.

621
00:52:02,756 --> 00:52:04,506
Hello? Sir?

622
00:52:05,548 --> 00:52:06,756
Sir...

623
00:52:06,839 --> 00:52:09,131
There was an SI named
Stephen in our station.

624
00:52:09,214 --> 00:52:10,714
But not now.

625
00:52:10,798 --> 00:52:12,589
30 years ago!

626
00:52:16,089 --> 00:52:18,964
He and his team went
missing in that forest.

627
00:52:19,339 --> 00:52:21,173
To be exact...

628
00:52:21,256 --> 00:52:23,673
It was on May 26, 1994.

629
00:52:27,381 --> 00:52:30,964
Stephen, Muthuvel,
Peter, Muniswami, Selvam.

630
00:52:31,048 --> 00:52:33,339
And that Muthuvel... is my father.

631
00:52:36,798 --> 00:52:39,548
After that, no one has ever seen them.

632
00:52:39,964 --> 00:52:41,756
To be very clear...

633
00:52:42,131 --> 00:52:44,839
There’s no way they’re still alive.

634
00:52:47,756 --> 00:52:49,631
Not just them...

635
00:52:49,714 --> 00:52:52,548
No one who went there
ever came back alive.

636
00:53:02,048 --> 00:53:04,214
Didn’t I warn you?

637
00:53:04,298 --> 00:53:06,506
That is a very dangerous place.

638
00:53:06,589 --> 00:53:08,548
Get out of there immediately.

639
00:53:10,548 --> 00:53:13,048
Muthuvel! Hey, Muthuvel! Can you hear me?

640
00:53:14,131 --> 00:53:17,339
Hey! Say something!

641
00:53:19,173 --> 00:53:21,506
Sir, are you coming? I’m leaving!

642
00:53:21,589 --> 00:53:23,464
Sir, maybe he got the wrong person.

643
00:53:23,548 --> 00:53:26,506
Otherwise, how can someone trapped
30 years ago speak to us now over this?

644
00:53:26,589 --> 00:53:28,173
Hey! Didn’t you hear what he said?

645
00:53:28,256 --> 00:53:29,631
Didn’t it sink into your head?

646
00:53:29,714 --> 00:53:33,298
Should we believe what someone told us,
or what we heard ourselves?

647
00:53:33,381 --> 00:53:35,298
I told you from the start, sir...

648
00:53:35,381 --> 00:53:37,464
We came here because of this moron!

649
00:53:37,548 --> 00:53:38,923
Sir, don’t abuse me for no reason.

650
00:53:39,006 --> 00:53:41,089
-What if I do?
-Try calling me then!

651
00:53:41,173 --> 00:53:43,089
-Come on!
-Move aside!

652
00:53:43,839 --> 00:53:46,798
Someone begging for his
life made us enter this forest!

653
00:53:46,881 --> 00:53:49,173
Ashokan won’t leave this
place unless this is resolved!

654
00:53:49,423 --> 00:53:52,256
Then you two stay and solve it yourselves!

655
00:53:54,631 --> 00:53:56,131
Hey, Reji!

656
00:53:56,214 --> 00:53:57,589
Hey!

657
00:53:58,673 --> 00:53:59,881
Sir, sir...

658
00:53:59,964 --> 00:54:01,923
There’s a big tree here…

659
00:54:02,006 --> 00:54:04,214
biggest one around.

660
00:54:04,298 --> 00:54:06,381
Covered in thick creepers…

661
00:54:06,464 --> 00:54:08,256
I’m right under it, sir.

662
00:54:08,714 --> 00:54:10,631
Sir, I'm here!

663
00:54:11,214 --> 00:54:12,923
Sir, can you hear me?

664
00:54:13,006 --> 00:54:14,214
Can you hear me!?

665
00:54:45,631 --> 00:54:46,589
Sir...

666
00:54:46,673 --> 00:54:48,798
Did you see the tree?

667
00:54:49,631 --> 00:54:51,881
Please say something, sir.

668
00:54:57,298 --> 00:54:59,214
Sir! Sir!

669
00:55:00,339 --> 00:55:02,339
There’s a body here, sir!

670
00:55:02,423 --> 00:55:04,881
I actually tripped on that and fell down.

671
00:55:04,964 --> 00:55:06,173
Sir...

672
00:55:06,256 --> 00:55:07,548
A body...

673
00:55:07,631 --> 00:55:09,423
It’s a policeman’s body, sir!

674
00:55:09,923 --> 00:55:12,089
That’s not our uniform…

675
00:55:12,173 --> 00:55:13,631
It’s Kerala Police.

676
00:55:13,714 --> 00:55:15,548
Kerala Police uniform!

677
00:55:17,131 --> 00:55:19,381
This looks like a middle-aged man, sir.

678
00:55:20,339 --> 00:55:22,839
This is the body of an Inspector.

679
00:55:22,923 --> 00:55:25,256
Name tag says Ashokan!

680
00:55:25,673 --> 00:55:27,339
M.G. Ashokan!

681
00:55:58,464 --> 00:55:59,423
Sir...

682
00:56:20,173 --> 00:56:22,589
Please say something, sir!

683
00:56:28,673 --> 00:56:31,673
Sir, we’re running out of time!

684
00:56:33,798 --> 00:56:35,131
Sir...

685
00:56:35,214 --> 00:56:36,881
When did you come here?

686
00:56:36,964 --> 00:56:38,923
It’s been around 2-3 hours.

687
00:56:39,881 --> 00:56:41,423
What’s today’s date?

688
00:56:41,506 --> 00:56:43,548
Why are you asking that now?

689
00:56:43,631 --> 00:56:44,964
Just tell me, sir!

690
00:56:45,048 --> 00:56:46,881
May 26th...

691
00:56:48,131 --> 00:56:50,048
Tell me the year, sir.

692
00:56:50,131 --> 00:56:52,298
1994.

693
00:57:59,714 --> 00:58:02,298
Hey, hurry up!

694
00:58:02,381 --> 00:58:04,048
Careful, Mum.

695
00:58:04,964 --> 00:58:06,131
Be careful.

696
00:58:12,756 --> 00:58:15,214
-Sir, where’s the ICU?
-That way.

697
00:58:15,298 --> 00:58:16,756
Come on, quick.

698
00:58:18,756 --> 00:58:20,839
-No, no.
-We want to see, sir.

699
00:58:20,923 --> 00:58:21,881
Why are you not letting us?

700
00:58:21,964 --> 00:58:23,131
What are you saying, sir?

701
00:58:23,631 --> 00:58:25,923
You can't see him. Leave with her.

702
00:58:26,006 --> 00:58:28,173
Please let us in, sir.

703
00:58:28,256 --> 00:58:29,464
Sir, we want to see, sir.

704
00:58:29,548 --> 00:58:31,548
No, just move away!

705
00:58:32,339 --> 00:58:33,631
Sir?

706
00:58:34,089 --> 00:58:35,048
Sir?

707
00:58:47,756 --> 00:58:50,048
-Hello?
-Sir...

708
00:58:50,131 --> 00:58:51,964
The man who was
admitted to the hospital...

709
00:58:52,048 --> 00:58:53,673
...has passed away.

710
00:58:55,756 --> 00:58:58,089
Sir, there’s another issue.

711
00:58:59,006 --> 00:59:00,048
What is it?

712
00:59:00,131 --> 00:59:02,214
Among the people who came
claiming to be his relatives,

713
00:59:02,298 --> 00:59:03,464
there was a woman as well.

714
00:59:03,548 --> 00:59:06,048
She looked to be around 50.

715
00:59:06,131 --> 00:59:07,798
She could be his mother.

716
00:59:07,881 --> 00:59:11,006
That’s what the hospital
staff assumed at first.

717
00:59:11,089 --> 00:59:12,714
But...

718
00:59:12,798 --> 00:59:14,214
she isn’t his mother.

719
00:59:17,839 --> 00:59:19,089
Then who is she?

720
00:59:19,173 --> 00:59:21,006
I want to see Peter. Let me go inside.

721
00:59:21,089 --> 00:59:22,256
Let us go in.

722
00:59:22,339 --> 00:59:24,798
You can’t create a scene here.
This is a hospital.

723
00:59:24,881 --> 00:59:27,089
Please take your mother and step outside.

724
00:59:27,173 --> 00:59:29,464
-Sir, I can’t.
-You can’t see him!

725
00:59:29,548 --> 00:59:30,964
This is a hospital.
Don’t create a disturbance!

726
00:59:31,048 --> 00:59:31,673
What’s going on?

727
00:59:32,923 --> 00:59:35,048
I need to see Peter,
but they won’t let me in.

728
00:59:35,131 --> 00:59:36,839
-What’s the problem?
-Sir...

729
00:59:36,923 --> 00:59:40,131
They claim to be relatives of Peter,
who was admitted after an accident.

730
00:59:40,214 --> 00:59:43,548
When I asked about their relation,
she said Peter is her husband.

731
00:59:44,506 --> 00:59:46,173
So what?

732
00:59:46,256 --> 00:59:47,423
Sir, didn’t you see him?

733
00:59:47,506 --> 00:59:49,589
Peter looks to be around 30 years.

734
00:59:49,673 --> 00:59:52,048
-This looks like a fraud case, sir.
-Hey! Fraud, is it!?

735
00:59:52,131 --> 00:59:53,839
-Who are you calling a fraud?
-Huh?

736
00:59:53,923 --> 00:59:55,506
Who did you just call a fraud?!

737
00:59:55,589 --> 00:59:57,381
We won’t allow this here.

738
00:59:57,464 --> 00:59:59,173
Quiet. Let me talk to them.

739
00:59:59,256 --> 01:00:00,673
What happened to your husband?

740
01:00:00,756 --> 01:00:02,673
He went missing in the forest.

741
01:00:02,756 --> 01:00:03,798
When?

742
01:00:03,881 --> 01:00:06,131
Thirty years ago.

743
01:00:06,214 --> 01:00:07,673
Thirty years!?

744
01:00:07,756 --> 01:00:10,214
Mum, the man inside barely 30 years old.

745
01:00:10,298 --> 01:00:11,423
He can’t be your husband.

746
01:00:11,506 --> 01:00:13,048
What? Are you mocking us?

747
01:00:13,131 --> 01:00:15,006
You were the ones
who called us here, right?

748
01:00:15,089 --> 01:00:17,298
Yes, that’s true.
But this isn’t your person.

749
01:00:17,381 --> 01:00:18,464
Wait a moment, sir.

750
01:00:18,631 --> 01:00:20,423
-You can’t see him just like that.
-Sir, sir...

751
01:00:20,506 --> 01:00:22,298
Isn't the man inside the same?

752
01:00:22,381 --> 01:00:24,548
It’s the same person.
Just take her and leave.

753
01:00:24,631 --> 01:00:25,631
Confirm it’s the same man?

754
01:00:25,714 --> 01:00:26,964
Confirm! Now leave!

755
01:00:27,048 --> 01:00:28,464
This is a hospital.
Don’t create trouble here!

756
01:00:28,548 --> 01:00:30,173
Sir, look at his date
of birth on this card.

757
01:00:30,256 --> 01:00:33,464
How can someone born in
1959 still be only 30 years old!?

758
01:00:36,506 --> 01:00:38,506
Sir… he is my father!

759
01:01:02,839 --> 01:01:04,298
Sir...

760
01:01:04,381 --> 01:01:06,381
They’re all confused.

761
01:01:08,923 --> 01:01:10,756
What do we do now, sir?

762
01:01:11,839 --> 01:01:13,173
Joshy...

763
01:01:13,464 --> 01:01:15,214
I’ll call you back, mate.

764
01:02:50,923 --> 01:02:52,548
Saneesh, tell me.

765
01:02:52,631 --> 01:02:53,673
Sir...

766
01:02:53,756 --> 01:02:56,464
The forensic team had arrived
and started their examination.

767
01:02:57,798 --> 01:02:59,048
Sir...

768
01:02:59,131 --> 01:03:00,506
Is Reji sir with you?

769
01:03:01,131 --> 01:03:02,256
No.

770
01:03:02,339 --> 01:03:05,381
Sir, that body doesn’t belong to
anyone from Perumalai station.

771
01:03:07,089 --> 01:03:08,839
That body looks...

772
01:03:08,923 --> 01:03:11,006
exactly like Reji sir.

773
01:03:13,798 --> 01:03:15,839
Saneesh, are you drunk!?

774
01:03:15,923 --> 01:03:16,714
No, sir.

775
01:03:17,131 --> 01:03:18,923
Is Rashid there?

776
01:03:19,006 --> 01:03:20,339
He’s not here, sir.

777
01:03:20,673 --> 01:03:22,006
Who else is there?

778
01:03:22,089 --> 01:03:23,214
Akash?

779
01:03:23,298 --> 01:03:25,298
-Yes, sir.
-Put him on the phone.

780
01:03:28,631 --> 01:03:29,756
Sir...

781
01:03:31,339 --> 01:03:33,381
Hey, what’s going on?

782
01:03:33,464 --> 01:03:35,506
Sir, even after cleaning the face...

783
01:03:35,589 --> 01:03:37,589
it still looked like Reji sir.

784
01:03:39,381 --> 01:03:41,256
But we still thought...

785
01:03:41,339 --> 01:03:43,381
it might be someone else.

786
01:03:43,464 --> 01:03:46,173
But when we found
the ID card in his purse--

787
01:03:57,089 --> 01:03:59,673
Sir, haven’t you seen Reji sir’s ring?

788
01:04:00,256 --> 01:04:01,923
Everything matches exactly.

789
01:04:02,006 --> 01:04:05,381
Akash, wasn’t Reji with us
when we went to see the body!?

790
01:04:05,464 --> 01:04:07,089
Weren’t you right there with me!?

791
01:04:07,173 --> 01:04:08,506
Yes, sir.

792
01:04:08,589 --> 01:04:11,214
Then what the hell is going on here!?

793
01:04:23,256 --> 01:04:24,964
Sir!

794
01:04:40,589 --> 01:04:41,548
Sir...

795
01:04:44,131 --> 01:04:45,506
Sir!

796
01:04:48,881 --> 01:04:50,381
Ashokan sir!

797
01:04:53,131 --> 01:04:55,006
Sir!

798
01:04:59,089 --> 01:05:01,256
SIR!

799
01:05:05,673 --> 01:05:07,131
Reji...

800
01:05:07,214 --> 01:05:08,423
Reji...

801
01:05:08,506 --> 01:05:09,506
Sir...

802
01:05:14,298 --> 01:05:16,298
Reji sir, grab my hand!

803
01:05:22,339 --> 01:05:24,548
Sir, hold my hand.

804
01:05:25,589 --> 01:05:27,214
Pull him up!

805
01:05:29,923 --> 01:05:30,714
Slowly.

806
01:05:30,923 --> 01:05:32,464
Give your hand.

807
01:05:39,839 --> 01:05:41,256
Reji, come on!

808
01:05:53,381 --> 01:05:54,089
Sir...

809
01:05:55,048 --> 01:05:57,423
Reji sir, give me your hand! Come on!

810
01:07:19,548 --> 01:07:21,006
Sir!

811
01:07:23,798 --> 01:07:25,381
Sir?

812
01:07:31,548 --> 01:07:32,881
Sir?

813
01:07:44,006 --> 01:07:45,631
James?

814
01:07:48,173 --> 01:07:50,339
James, where are you?

815
01:07:51,673 --> 01:07:54,714
Don’t play with me. Come to me.

816
01:07:59,006 --> 01:08:00,714
James?

817
01:08:00,798 --> 01:08:02,464
Are you there?

818
01:08:13,214 --> 01:08:14,964
Who are you?

819
01:09:10,756 --> 01:09:12,506
What happened?

820
01:09:12,589 --> 01:09:13,673
My brother...

821
01:09:13,756 --> 01:09:14,631
My brother...

822
01:09:14,714 --> 01:09:16,798
He’s missing.

823
01:09:19,548 --> 01:09:21,506
Don’t cry. We’ll find him.

824
01:09:23,589 --> 01:09:25,339
Wait here, alright?

825
01:10:27,256 --> 01:10:28,714
Dear, go!

826
01:10:31,464 --> 01:10:32,798
Go!

827
01:10:38,839 --> 01:10:40,214
Hey!

828
01:11:43,089 --> 01:11:44,631
Who are you!?

829
01:11:44,714 --> 01:11:45,964
Sir, I’m police.

830
01:11:46,048 --> 01:11:48,089
CPO from Velloorkadu station.

831
01:11:50,131 --> 01:11:51,798
I’m Stephen George.

832
01:11:52,131 --> 01:11:53,923
SI, Perumalai station.

833
01:11:55,756 --> 01:11:57,839
Accused escaped from our bus.

834
01:11:57,923 --> 01:11:59,589
I’m searching for them.

835
01:12:02,173 --> 01:12:03,214
Sir!

836
01:12:03,298 --> 01:12:04,673
What’s today’s date?

837
01:12:04,756 --> 01:12:05,964
May 26th.

838
01:12:06,798 --> 01:12:08,464
And what year is it?

839
01:12:08,548 --> 01:12:10,214
What? I didn’t get you.

840
01:12:10,298 --> 01:12:12,631
I asked, what year is this?

841
01:12:12,839 --> 01:12:14,839
Are you playing games!?

842
01:12:14,923 --> 01:12:16,298
Please, sir.

843
01:12:16,756 --> 01:12:19,256
1994. So what now?

844
01:12:36,464 --> 01:12:38,423
Sir, please save me!

845
01:12:38,798 --> 01:12:40,048
Sir!

846
01:12:40,506 --> 01:12:41,339
Sir!

847
01:12:41,423 --> 01:12:42,589
Sir...

848
01:12:44,048 --> 01:12:45,423
Muthuvel...

849
01:12:45,506 --> 01:12:46,256
Sir...

850
01:12:48,339 --> 01:12:50,131
-Sir, sir.
-What happened, Muthuvel?

851
01:12:50,214 --> 01:12:51,298
These guys!

852
01:12:51,923 --> 01:12:53,839
Hey, calm down and surrender yourself!

853
01:12:53,923 --> 01:12:54,881
Kill him!

854
01:14:42,423 --> 01:14:44,214
Who are you!?

855
01:15:01,173 --> 01:15:02,756
James...

856
01:15:07,006 --> 01:15:08,423
James?

857
01:15:09,214 --> 01:15:11,714
Where are you hiding?

858
01:15:13,256 --> 01:15:15,381
Don't be scared.

859
01:15:19,464 --> 01:15:20,756
Come fast.

860
01:15:21,548 --> 01:15:22,548
James...

861
01:15:24,339 --> 01:15:25,839
Darling...

862
01:15:36,964 --> 01:15:38,631
James...

863
01:15:39,048 --> 01:15:41,548
Why are you so scared?

864
01:15:42,214 --> 01:15:43,673
Come to me.

865
01:15:43,756 --> 01:15:46,964
Come and kiss me
just like our first time.

866
01:15:47,423 --> 01:15:50,006
Come on! Get up!

867
01:16:46,756 --> 01:16:48,964
Sir, you look absolutely terrified.

868
01:16:51,923 --> 01:16:53,714
Don’t worry, sir.

869
01:16:53,798 --> 01:16:56,173
There are no ghosts
roaming in this forest.

870
01:16:58,089 --> 01:16:59,589
Who are you?

871
01:17:00,423 --> 01:17:02,173
Sir, what exactly do you want to know?

872
01:17:02,256 --> 01:17:04,006
Who I am or what is happening here?

873
01:17:08,256 --> 01:17:11,089
Sir, did you notice an
idol on your way here?

874
01:17:11,173 --> 01:17:12,798
Did you observe its head?

875
01:17:13,214 --> 01:17:15,214
It was shaped like a crow.

876
01:17:17,798 --> 01:17:22,006
Since entering this forest,
have you seen even a single crow?

877
01:17:23,548 --> 01:17:25,048
No!

878
01:17:25,131 --> 01:17:28,673
Every problem that happens
here revolves around that.

879
01:17:32,506 --> 01:17:35,589
The origin of all this
goes back many years.

880
01:17:36,964 --> 01:17:38,506
To be precise…

881
01:17:38,589 --> 01:17:41,131
to the time when the
Portuguese first arrived here.

882
01:17:43,964 --> 01:17:45,173
Back then…

883
01:17:45,256 --> 01:17:50,339
this idol was worshipped by a
specific tribe living in this forest.

884
01:17:52,048 --> 01:17:55,756
They believed crows as the symbol of God.

885
01:17:58,131 --> 01:18:00,423
They would circle around this idol,

886
01:18:00,506 --> 01:18:04,298
praying for prosperity for themselves
and their future generations.

887
01:18:05,381 --> 01:18:09,923
If pregnant women prayed
here and fed the crows…

888
01:18:10,006 --> 01:18:14,339
they believed their unborn child
would be blessed with prosperity.

889
01:18:15,881 --> 01:18:19,089
When Portuguese dominance
reached its peak…

890
01:18:19,381 --> 01:18:23,589
Lord Gabriel Antonio,
a rationalist who ruled this region…

891
01:18:23,673 --> 01:18:28,673
decided to erase every belief
that existed here until then.

892
01:18:30,381 --> 01:18:32,631
He followed only one ideology.

893
01:18:32,714 --> 01:18:35,089
“Praise only for the King!”

894
01:18:35,214 --> 01:18:37,964
Worship was meant for the King alone.

895
01:18:40,006 --> 01:18:42,631
He destroyed every place of worship here…

896
01:18:42,714 --> 01:18:45,964
and smuggled the valuable
idols out of this land.

897
01:18:47,339 --> 01:18:52,589
Eventually, news about
this little-known tribe…

898
01:18:52,714 --> 01:18:55,673
and their unique form of
worship reached the King.

899
01:18:55,756 --> 01:18:59,506
So he entered this forest
with his full army.

900
01:18:59,589 --> 01:19:01,256
To seize that idol!

901
01:19:04,089 --> 01:19:08,464
No matter how much the tribe pleaded,
he refused to listen.

902
01:19:08,714 --> 01:19:13,589
He ordered his forces to take
that idol away at any cost.

903
01:19:17,089 --> 01:19:19,298
But no matter how hard they tried…

904
01:19:19,381 --> 01:19:21,214
they simply couldn’t move it.

905
01:19:22,798 --> 01:19:24,173
Furious at this,

906
01:19:24,256 --> 01:19:26,589
the King ordered the
massacre of the tribe,

907
01:19:26,673 --> 01:19:29,381
hacking them down and
shooting them mercilessly.

908
01:19:30,923 --> 01:19:33,214
Even that wasn’t enough for him.

909
01:19:33,298 --> 01:19:36,506
He burned every crow in this forest.

910
01:19:39,756 --> 01:19:42,923
That bloodshed… was where
everything truly began.

911
01:19:44,089 --> 01:19:46,423
The people believed…

912
01:19:46,506 --> 01:19:49,964
their deity would bring them
prosperity and good fortune.

913
01:19:50,464 --> 01:19:51,673
But…

914
01:19:51,756 --> 01:19:56,214
no one realised it also
had power over time itself.

915
01:20:00,048 --> 01:20:05,173
The King and his forces took nearly an hour
to reach the temple through this forest.

916
01:20:05,256 --> 01:20:07,298
But after that massacre…

917
01:20:07,381 --> 01:20:10,548
they couldn’t find their way
out, even after a full day.

918
01:20:11,381 --> 01:20:13,423
One day turned into several days…

919
01:20:13,506 --> 01:20:14,714
then months…

920
01:20:14,798 --> 01:20:16,298
and eventually years.

921
01:20:17,923 --> 01:20:22,089
Would you believe me if I said they are
still trapped, circling this forest?

922
01:20:24,923 --> 01:20:28,089
The moment blood touched
this soil that day…

923
01:20:28,173 --> 01:20:30,964
the deity that had once
been calm and serene…

924
01:20:31,048 --> 01:20:33,214
transformed into a fierce, wrathful force.

925
01:20:35,506 --> 01:20:39,048
From then on, every time
blood was spilled here…

926
01:20:39,131 --> 01:20:41,631
and whenever sound crossed
a certain limit…

927
01:20:42,506 --> 01:20:46,173
even time itself would begin
to distort in this place.

928
01:20:49,048 --> 01:20:52,673
Everyone you saw or heard
here is not dead, sir…

929
01:20:52,756 --> 01:20:55,548
they are people trapped inside this loop.

930
01:20:56,381 --> 01:20:58,839
From different eras of time.

931
01:22:03,173 --> 01:22:05,089
How do you know all this?

932
01:22:06,798 --> 01:22:10,256
I was the one who betrayed these people
and brought the King here.

933
01:22:10,339 --> 01:22:12,631
A spy for the Portuguese army.

934
01:22:14,298 --> 01:22:16,964
The main reason
behind this entire disaster!

935
01:22:24,589 --> 01:22:25,756
Sir!

936
01:22:25,839 --> 01:22:26,923
Sir!

937
01:22:28,089 --> 01:22:31,464
There is only one way to escape this, sir.

938
01:22:32,881 --> 01:22:36,048
The incident that brought me,
you, and everyone else here…

939
01:22:36,131 --> 01:22:37,964
must never happen!

940
01:22:39,423 --> 01:22:41,756
Until we stop it…

941
01:22:41,839 --> 01:22:44,214
we will remain trapped in this loop!

942
01:22:58,798 --> 01:22:59,673
Sir!

943
01:23:00,339 --> 01:23:01,423
Ashokan sir!

944
01:23:12,006 --> 01:23:13,714
SIR!

945
01:23:24,631 --> 01:23:26,298
-Reji!
-Sir!

946
01:23:30,131 --> 01:23:31,881
Reji!

947
01:23:32,464 --> 01:23:33,714
Sir!

948
01:23:40,631 --> 01:23:43,256
Sir, give me your hand.

949
01:23:46,964 --> 01:23:48,298
Sir!

950
01:23:55,048 --> 01:23:58,006
Reji sir, come on, hold the hand!

951
01:25:54,964 --> 01:25:56,131
Hey!

952
01:25:58,089 --> 01:25:59,756
Hey, stop!

953
01:26:01,589 --> 01:26:03,423
Where are you going?

954
01:26:06,131 --> 01:26:07,423
Hey!

955
01:26:16,589 --> 01:26:18,214
Chechi!

956
01:27:22,256 --> 01:27:23,839
Reji!

957
01:27:25,089 --> 01:27:26,381
Chechi!

958
01:27:26,464 --> 01:27:28,131
Hey, wait!

959
01:27:28,214 --> 01:27:29,381
Chechi…

960
01:27:33,339 --> 01:27:34,631
Please stop.

961
01:27:42,173 --> 01:27:43,798
-Muthuvel!
-Sir!

962
01:27:57,339 --> 01:27:58,214
Sir!

963
01:28:07,798 --> 01:28:08,964
Sir!

964
01:28:09,798 --> 01:28:11,131
Reji sir!

965
01:28:13,756 --> 01:28:15,298
Sir, wait!

966
01:28:25,756 --> 01:28:27,006
Hey!

967
01:29:19,798 --> 01:29:20,881
Sir…

968
01:29:20,964 --> 01:29:23,256
Please don’t shoot.
I’ll explain everything.

969
01:29:37,881 --> 01:29:39,714
Sir, I’m from the Kerala Police.

970
01:29:39,798 --> 01:29:41,423
You need to leave this place immediately.

971
01:29:41,714 --> 01:29:43,173
Why, sir?

972
01:29:43,256 --> 01:29:45,006
The accused escaped from
our custody during transport.

973
01:29:45,089 --> 01:29:46,131
We are searching for them.

974
01:29:46,214 --> 01:29:47,631
We can deal with that later, sir.

975
01:29:47,714 --> 01:29:49,048
First, you must leave this place.

976
01:29:49,131 --> 01:29:50,089
I can’t do that, sir.

977
01:29:50,173 --> 01:29:53,131
Those rascals fired at
two policemen on duty.

978
01:29:53,214 --> 01:29:55,673
Should we spare them
after crossing such limits?

979
01:29:55,881 --> 01:29:57,631
Sir, please try to understand.

980
01:29:57,714 --> 01:29:59,214
This is a dangerous place!

981
01:29:59,298 --> 01:30:00,256
What is it, sir?

982
01:30:00,339 --> 01:30:03,006
Are you also going to
repeat that stupid ghost story?

983
01:30:04,256 --> 01:30:05,464
Sir!

984
01:30:05,548 --> 01:30:09,589
If you don’t leave now, you will
never see your wife and child again.

985
01:30:11,298 --> 01:30:13,506
You are going to have a baby.

986
01:30:13,589 --> 01:30:14,756
A baby boy.

987
01:30:14,839 --> 01:30:16,339
Who are you!?

988
01:30:18,839 --> 01:30:20,714
How do you know all this?

989
01:30:20,839 --> 01:30:23,714
My name is Anand.
My mother’s name is Sethulakshmi.

990
01:30:23,798 --> 01:30:25,006
I don’t have a father.

991
01:30:25,089 --> 01:30:27,006
I haven't seen him until now.

992
01:30:27,089 --> 01:30:28,964
I don’t even know what happened to him.

993
01:30:29,048 --> 01:30:29,923
But…

994
01:30:30,006 --> 01:30:31,756
I’m starting to understand it,
piece by piece.

995
01:30:31,923 --> 01:30:35,173
He went missing in
this forest 30 years ago.

996
01:30:35,256 --> 01:30:36,756
And he never returned.

997
01:30:36,839 --> 01:30:39,548
I have only seen my father in photographs.

998
01:30:39,631 --> 01:30:41,506
This is my father.

999
01:30:41,589 --> 01:30:43,131
Stephen George!

1000
01:30:56,548 --> 01:30:57,673
Oh…

1001
01:30:57,798 --> 01:30:59,631
Do you need more proof?

1002
01:31:03,464 --> 01:31:05,881
May 26th, 1994.

1003
01:31:05,964 --> 01:31:07,673
My date of birth.

1004
01:31:07,756 --> 01:31:09,964
The day your son was born.

1005
01:31:19,756 --> 01:31:22,673
Now, the bats will start
screeching together.

1006
01:31:29,839 --> 01:31:32,548
And you will hear a sound from that side.

1007
01:31:34,006 --> 01:31:37,923
They are going to choke one of
the cops from your team to death.

1008
01:31:39,589 --> 01:31:41,631
If you go there right now…

1009
01:31:41,714 --> 01:31:43,131
you can save him.

1010
01:31:43,214 --> 01:31:44,173
But…

1011
01:31:44,256 --> 01:31:46,631
the moment you fire your gun…

1012
01:31:46,714 --> 01:31:49,173
everything will begin
again from square one.

1013
01:31:49,631 --> 01:31:51,756
Sir, save me!

1014
01:32:21,173 --> 01:32:22,881
-Muthuvel!
-Sir!

1015
01:32:23,964 --> 01:32:25,506
What happened, Muthuvel?

1016
01:32:25,589 --> 01:32:27,006
Sir, sir!

1017
01:32:27,089 --> 01:32:28,089
Them!

1018
01:32:36,089 --> 01:32:37,131
Hey!

1019
01:32:37,214 --> 01:32:38,839
We can’t just let them go, sir.

1020
01:32:38,964 --> 01:32:40,464
Why can’t you understand?

1021
01:32:40,548 --> 01:32:42,214
Let’s catch them once we get out of here.

1022
01:32:42,298 --> 01:32:44,173
Right now, all of us need
to leave this place first.

1023
01:32:47,881 --> 01:32:50,006
Please… we need to get out of here.

1024
01:32:50,089 --> 01:32:51,923
Call the others who are with you.

1025
01:32:52,006 --> 01:32:53,714
Please don’t shoot under any circumstance.

1026
01:32:53,798 --> 01:32:55,923
No blood should touch this ground.

1027
01:33:04,131 --> 01:33:05,256
Peter…

1028
01:33:05,339 --> 01:33:09,506
If you move a little ahead from
where we split, there’s a temple.

1029
01:33:09,589 --> 01:33:11,173
Come there quickly. Over.

1030
01:33:11,256 --> 01:33:13,006
Okay, sir. Over.

1031
01:33:13,089 --> 01:33:16,006
Don’t tell sir about Selva for now.

1032
01:33:17,381 --> 01:33:19,964
If he finds out,
he won’t leave without catching them.

1033
01:33:20,048 --> 01:33:21,089
But what if he asks?

1034
01:33:21,214 --> 01:33:22,923
We’ll make something up if so.

1035
01:33:46,048 --> 01:33:47,256
Sir…

1036
01:33:47,339 --> 01:33:48,756
Which way should we go from here?

1037
01:33:48,839 --> 01:33:53,089
No matter which way we go from here,
we should be able to reach the road, sir.

1038
01:33:53,423 --> 01:33:54,881
Move ahead.

1039
01:34:42,214 --> 01:34:43,506
Sir!

1040
01:34:57,923 --> 01:35:00,923
Sir, let’s try going through this route.

1041
01:35:04,464 --> 01:35:05,881
Come on, sir.

1042
01:35:06,548 --> 01:35:07,881
Anand…

1043
01:35:37,631 --> 01:35:38,923
Careful.

1044
01:37:05,714 --> 01:37:08,339
Sir, maybe we should split up and move.

1045
01:37:08,423 --> 01:37:10,548
You take that route. We’ll go this way.

1046
01:37:11,673 --> 01:37:12,673
Anand…

1047
01:37:13,631 --> 01:37:14,631
Be careful.

1048
01:37:15,256 --> 01:37:16,256
Come.

1049
01:38:25,298 --> 01:38:29,131
Didn’t I already warn you we’d be in
serious trouble if we came here, sir?

1050
01:38:29,589 --> 01:38:32,381
So, is there really no
way out of this place, sir?

1051
01:38:55,548 --> 01:38:58,631
I know someone who actually
made it out of here alive.

1052
01:40:29,673 --> 01:40:33,089
Didn’t you say we could get out no
matter which direction we walked?

1053
01:40:33,298 --> 01:40:36,214
Now let’s try circling around this one.

1054
01:40:39,964 --> 01:40:40,964
Come on, let’s move.

1055
01:41:46,173 --> 01:41:47,298
Hello?

1056
01:41:54,256 --> 01:41:55,339
Sir...

1057
01:41:55,881 --> 01:41:58,506
I think we’ve reached
somewhere close to the road.

1058
01:42:36,923 --> 01:42:38,256
Where’s Muthuvel?

1059
01:42:38,464 --> 01:42:39,964
Muthuvel!

1060
01:42:41,964 --> 01:42:43,548
Hey, Muthuvel!

1061
01:42:49,298 --> 01:42:50,464
Muthuvel...

1062
01:42:50,548 --> 01:42:51,548
Muthuvel!

1063
01:42:52,298 --> 01:42:53,756
Hey, Muthuvel!

1064
01:43:06,631 --> 01:43:07,964
Sir...

1065
01:43:08,048 --> 01:43:09,589
We shouldn’t stay here any longer.

1066
01:43:09,673 --> 01:43:10,464
Come.

1067
01:43:11,798 --> 01:43:13,256
Let’s go.

1068
01:43:48,089 --> 01:43:50,464
From now on, we move only as a group!

1069
01:44:05,923 --> 01:44:07,006
Hey!

1070
01:45:28,381 --> 01:45:31,006
Peter, are you alright?

1071
01:46:04,339 --> 01:46:05,589
Come on, you!

1072
01:47:26,006 --> 01:47:27,881
Sir, let’s move.

1073
01:47:30,589 --> 01:47:32,881
Anand, come on, let’s go.

1074
01:47:50,589 --> 01:47:51,756
Hey, Peter!

1075
01:47:52,339 --> 01:47:53,423
Peter...

1076
01:47:54,506 --> 01:47:55,923
Peter!

1077
01:47:56,131 --> 01:47:58,048
What happened, Peter?

1078
01:48:00,048 --> 01:48:01,923
Hey, Peter!

1079
01:48:02,548 --> 01:48:04,381
I can’t move forward, sir.

1080
01:48:15,714 --> 01:48:16,881
Peter...

1081
01:48:16,964 --> 01:48:19,048
I’m fine now, sir.

1082
01:48:21,714 --> 01:48:23,173
Get up.

1083
01:50:51,589 --> 01:50:52,339
Sir...

1084
01:50:52,423 --> 01:50:53,589
It’s coming from that side, sir.

1085
01:50:53,673 --> 01:50:54,673
Come.

1086
01:50:56,131 --> 01:50:57,131
Sir...

1087
01:50:57,214 --> 01:50:58,381
Isn’t it coming from that direction?

1088
01:51:10,423 --> 01:51:12,423
Sir, I’m certain it’s from there.

1089
01:51:17,006 --> 01:51:18,506
Yes, it’s from there.

1090
01:51:18,964 --> 01:51:21,131
Hey, he’s trying to confuse us, sir!

1091
01:51:30,756 --> 01:51:32,631
It’s from this side, Anand.

1092
01:51:33,131 --> 01:51:35,256
Sir, we just heard the sound from there.

1093
01:51:35,381 --> 01:51:37,381
Who are you? Why are you misleading us?

1094
01:51:37,464 --> 01:51:38,089
Hey, Peter!

1095
01:51:38,173 --> 01:51:39,048
Just listen to me.

1096
01:51:39,131 --> 01:51:40,298
Who the hell is he, sir?

1097
01:51:40,381 --> 01:51:42,089
Why are you even trusting him?

1098
01:51:42,173 --> 01:51:44,048
We’ve come this far
because of what you said...

1099
01:51:44,131 --> 01:51:45,881
Everyone who was with us is dead.

1100
01:51:45,964 --> 01:51:47,381
Now it’s just us left.

1101
01:51:47,464 --> 01:51:49,173
Do you want us dead too?

1102
01:51:50,506 --> 01:51:52,964
That crow’s call came
from that side, right?

1103
01:51:53,548 --> 01:51:54,714
Come on!

1104
01:52:48,673 --> 01:52:52,006
What? Couldn’t you
find any better way to die?

1105
01:52:52,089 --> 01:52:53,589
We are police officers, man!

1106
01:52:55,381 --> 01:52:56,756
What’s today’s date?

1107
01:52:56,839 --> 01:52:59,131
Sir... May... 26th.

1108
01:52:59,214 --> 01:53:01,214
-Year?
-’94, sir.

1109
01:53:03,048 --> 01:53:05,673
Sir, is there some problem?

1110
01:53:06,631 --> 01:53:07,798
Get in.

1111
01:53:13,298 --> 01:53:14,631
Careful.

1112
01:53:14,714 --> 01:53:16,006
Anand, aren’t you coming?

1113
01:53:16,089 --> 01:53:18,256
I can’t survive here like this.

1114
01:53:23,048 --> 01:53:24,673
Go and see your baby.

1115
01:53:24,756 --> 01:53:26,506
Stay with him.

1116
01:53:28,256 --> 01:53:30,964
Growing up without a father is very hard.

1117
01:54:51,339 --> 01:54:52,673
Anand...

1118
01:54:54,631 --> 01:54:56,298
what happened?

1119
01:55:00,173 --> 01:55:01,881
Nothing.

1120
01:55:03,548 --> 01:55:05,964
Neethu's bystander?

1121
01:55:09,464 --> 01:55:10,548
Dad...

1122
01:55:22,381 --> 01:55:23,798
Its a girl.

1123
01:55:24,714 --> 01:55:26,631
-Neethu?
-She's fine.

1124
01:55:50,423 --> 01:55:53,006
Sir, which station were
you posted at before this?

1125
01:55:53,089 --> 01:55:54,214
Udayamperoor.

1126
01:55:54,298 --> 01:55:55,339
Oh...

1127
01:55:55,423 --> 01:55:57,131
Benny sir is still there, right?

1128
01:55:57,214 --> 01:55:58,214
Yeah. How do you know him?

1129
01:55:58,298 --> 01:56:00,673
I was posted there in 2019.

1130
01:56:00,756 --> 01:56:02,964
It’s been a long time
since I spoke to him.

1131
01:56:03,048 --> 01:56:04,131
How long have you been here?

1132
01:56:04,214 --> 01:56:05,714
Almost a year.

1133
01:56:05,798 --> 01:56:07,631
It’s very peaceful here, sir.

1134
01:56:08,339 --> 01:56:10,381
Is Perumalai station nearby?

1135
01:56:10,464 --> 01:56:11,464
Yes, sir.

1136
01:56:11,923 --> 01:56:14,923
Sir, after this border, it’s their area.

1137
01:56:15,006 --> 01:56:16,131
Why did you ask, sir?

1138
01:56:16,214 --> 01:56:18,214
My dad was an inspector there.

1139
01:56:18,506 --> 01:56:20,298
Is your dad a Tamilian?

1140
01:56:20,381 --> 01:56:22,464
So you must know Tamil very well, right?

1141
01:56:22,548 --> 01:56:23,423
No...

1142
01:56:23,548 --> 01:56:25,214
My mom is a Malayali.

1143
01:56:25,298 --> 01:56:27,339
I’ve been in Kerala since childhood.

1144
01:56:28,673 --> 01:56:31,214
Sir, isn’t that Ashokan sir’s car?

1145
01:56:31,423 --> 01:56:33,173
Yes, it is.

1146
01:56:36,589 --> 01:56:37,673
Sir...

1147
01:56:37,756 --> 01:56:39,423
What happened, sir?

1148
01:56:41,548 --> 01:56:43,173
My car broke down, man.

1149
01:56:44,256 --> 01:56:45,798
Sir... our new SI.

1150
01:56:46,423 --> 01:56:49,006
Sir, I’m Ashokan.

1151
01:56:49,298 --> 01:56:51,589
I received a mail saying
you’d be joining today.

1152
01:56:51,673 --> 01:56:54,673
I started earlier to reach there,
but my car ran into trouble.

1153
01:56:54,756 --> 01:56:56,589
Rajesh from the workshop
will be here soon...

1154
01:56:56,673 --> 01:56:59,881
Once he arrives, get this fixed
and take the car to the station.

1155
01:56:59,964 --> 01:57:02,173
-Okay, sir.
-Sir, I’ll also come to the station.

1156
01:57:03,339 --> 01:57:05,089
Call me if there's anything.

1157
01:57:05,173 --> 01:57:06,298
Let’s go.

1158
01:57:10,506 --> 01:57:12,506
Sir, where is your hometown?

1159
01:57:12,589 --> 01:57:13,923
Kochi.

1160
01:57:14,006 --> 01:57:14,798
Oh!

1161
01:57:14,881 --> 01:57:16,756
So you’re a Kochi folk?

1162
01:57:18,298 --> 01:57:20,298
Sir, your family?

1163
01:57:20,631 --> 01:57:22,839
Mom, dad, wife, and daughter.

1164
01:57:23,173 --> 01:57:25,006
How old is your daughter?

1165
01:57:25,881 --> 01:57:27,756
She was born recently.

1166
01:57:27,839 --> 01:57:29,964
Wow, then you owe us a treat, sir!

1167
01:57:32,214 --> 01:57:33,923
Yes, Rasheed, tell me.

1168
01:57:34,006 --> 01:57:35,131
Sir, there’s an issue.

1169
01:57:35,339 --> 01:57:36,631
What issue?

1170
01:57:36,714 --> 01:57:39,006
While passing through the forest road...

1171
01:57:39,089 --> 01:57:42,089
We noticed a vehicle parked
suspiciously and checked it.

1172
01:57:42,173 --> 01:57:44,256
Some youngsters were inside.

1173
01:57:44,339 --> 01:57:47,256
They were trying to shoot a video.
They’re Tamilians, sir.

1174
01:57:47,548 --> 01:57:49,923
There are 1-2 girls with them as well.

1175
01:57:50,006 --> 01:57:51,631
Sir, he has stepped in and blocked them!

1176
01:57:51,714 --> 01:57:52,714
Who? Reji?

1177
01:57:52,798 --> 01:57:53,548
Yes, sir.

1178
01:57:53,631 --> 01:57:56,381
Looks like those guys have
some influence over higher officials.

1179
01:57:56,464 --> 01:57:57,798
I don’t think I can handle this alone.

1180
01:57:57,881 --> 01:57:59,589
Sir, can you come here quickly?

1181
01:58:00,714 --> 01:58:03,048
What’s wrong with him?

1182
01:58:29,298 --> 01:58:32,298
-What happened, sir?
-No, nothing.

1183
01:58:34,923 --> 01:58:37,089
Shouldn’t you be more careful, man!?

1184
01:59:12,173 --> 01:59:13,798
Are you okay?

1185
01:59:13,881 --> 01:59:15,798
Are you okay?

1186
01:59:17,964 --> 01:59:19,881
Hello? Hello?

1187
01:59:19,964 --> 01:59:21,756
Are you okay?

1188
01:59:29,464 --> 01:59:31,298
Come, help me!

1189
01:59:32,798 --> 01:59:34,839
Sir, open the door!

1190
01:59:36,673 --> 01:59:38,506
Move inside, move inside!

1191
01:59:38,589 --> 01:59:40,298
Sir, move inside!

1192
01:59:42,881 --> 01:59:44,464
Go, start the vehicle quickly!

1193
01:59:57,631 --> 01:59:59,006
Hey, breathe.
-Have you seen this girl before?

1194
01:59:59,089 --> 01:59:59,423
No, sir.

1195
01:59:59,506 --> 02:00:01,131
Sir, go faster!

1196
02:00:01,214 --> 02:00:03,298
Hey, open your eyes!

1197
02:00:03,381 --> 02:00:05,173
Floor it, man!

1198
02:00:05,256 --> 02:00:08,714
Sir, take her phone. Check her
recent calls and contact someone.

1199
02:00:09,548 --> 02:00:11,298
Go, go!

1200
02:00:28,298 --> 02:00:29,589
Hey!

1201
02:00:33,131 --> 02:00:34,256
Hey!

1202
02:00:35,756 --> 02:00:37,298
Dad...

1203
02:00:48,298 --> 02:00:49,256
Hey!

1204
02:01:03,964 --> 02:01:06,214
Sir, stop the vehicle.

1205
02:01:54,214 --> 02:01:55,256
Hello?

1206
02:01:55,339 --> 02:01:56,464
Neethu...

1207
02:01:56,548 --> 02:01:57,839
Where is our daughter?

1208
02:01:58,714 --> 02:02:01,214
I’m trying to make her sleep,
but she’s very cranky.

1209
02:02:01,298 --> 02:02:02,756
Did you reach there?

1210
02:02:04,923 --> 02:02:06,089
Hello?

1211
02:02:06,839 --> 02:02:08,714
Can’t you hear me?

1212
02:02:08,798 --> 02:02:09,923
Hello?

1213
02:02:10,006 --> 02:02:11,298
What happened?

1214
02:02:12,756 --> 02:02:13,548
Nothing.

1215
02:02:13,631 --> 02:02:15,548
Hey, are you okay?

1216
02:02:40,506 --> 02:02:43,506
There is only one way to escape this, sir.

1217
02:02:44,089 --> 02:02:47,298
The incident that brought me,
you, and everyone else here…

1218
02:02:47,381 --> 02:02:48,714
must not happen!

1219
02:02:53,673 --> 02:02:55,673
Until we stop it...

1220
02:02:55,756 --> 02:02:58,464
we will remain trapped in this loop!

1221
02:04:00,589 --> 02:04:05,048
♪ The stars obey his silent call ♪

1222
02:04:07,506 --> 02:04:11,423
♪ The night kneels, the ages fall ♪

1223
02:04:13,548 --> 02:04:18,464
♪ He turns the wheel no eye can see ♪

1224
02:04:20,006 --> 02:04:24,214
♪ The past and future bend to decree ♪

1225
02:04:26,423 --> 02:04:30,048
♪ With time, the incident
faded into deeper layers ♪

1226
02:04:30,131 --> 02:04:34,506
♪ You are the time,
and you are the end of it all ♪

1227
02:04:39,506 --> 02:04:43,423
♪ With time, the incident
faded into deeper layers ♪

1228
02:04:43,506 --> 02:04:47,506
♪ You are the time,
and you are the end of it all ♪

1229
02:05:33,506 --> 02:05:37,339
♪ Every breath a moment dies ♪

1230
02:05:40,381 --> 02:05:44,381
♪ Every blink a world replies ♪

1231
02:05:46,423 --> 02:05:50,548
♪ He weaves the hours with silent thread ♪

1232
02:05:53,089 --> 02:05:57,839
♪ Between the living and the dead ♪

1233
02:05:59,381 --> 02:06:01,673
♪ O' the god of time ♪

1234
02:06:02,714 --> 02:06:06,048
♪ O' the supreme one ♪

1235
02:06:06,131 --> 02:06:11,339
♪ who burns eternal within the darkness ♪

1236
02:06:48,714 --> 02:06:53,881
♪ When he sleeps, time dies ♪

1237
02:06:54,006 --> 02:07:00,381
♪ When he wakes, the worlds arise ♪
